The paper is about machine ethics and the development of artificial moral agents, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of these agents, which could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO). The ethical considerations and potential societal impacts of AMAs could also fall under the categories of ethics and technology (cs.ET), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
